addr="larsbirkedal">Lars Birkedal</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00OI</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>An extreme point in the design space...</fr:p>
 <jms-indent:block
xmlns:jms-indent="jonmsterling:indenting">
  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>\mathsf {ref} \colon   \mathbf {type} \to \mathbf {type}</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>\mathsf {new} \colon  A \to   \mathsf {T} \, { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {ref} \, A \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>\mathsf {get} \colon   \mathsf {ref} \, A \to \mathsf {T} \, A</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>\mathsf {set} \colon  { \mathsf {ref}   \, A} \times  A \to   \mathsf {T} \, { \mathopen {} \left ( \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

 </jms-indent:block>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Deeply impredicative:</fr:strong> heap contains elements of <fr:em>arbitrary</fr:em> types.</fr:p><fr:p><fr:tex>\Longrightarrow</fr:tex> guarded recursion (step-indexing) used to break the circularity.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
