href="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022">S., Gratzer, and Birkedal (2022)</fr:link> found synthetic denotational semantics for guarded higher-order dynamic allocation in an impredicative version of guarded dependent type theory (<fr:strong>iGDTT</fr:strong>).</fr:p>
 <jms-indent:block
xmlns:jms-indent="jonmsterling:indenting">
  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \llbracket \mathbf {type} \rrbracket \mathclose {}}  =  \mathsf {Fun} { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {World} ,{ \mathbf {Set} } \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>\mathsf {World}  =  \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( L: \mathbf {FinSet} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( L: \mathbf {FinSet} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( L: \mathbf {FinSet} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( L: \mathbf {FinSet} \right ) \mathclose {}} } } { \mathopen {} \left ( L \to  { \color {red} \mathord { \blacktriangleright } } { \mathopen {} \llbracket \mathbf {type} \rrbracket \mathclose {}} \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row>
   <fr:tex>      \mathsf {Heap}  =      \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( w: \mathsf {World} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( w: \mathsf {World} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( w: \mathsf {World} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( w: \mathsf {World} \right ) \mathclose {}} } }       \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( l: \pi _1w \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( l: \pi _1w \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( l: \pi _1w \right ) \mathclose {}} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ { \mathopen {} \left ( l: \pi _1w \right ) \mathclose {}} } }      { \color {red} \mathord { \blacktriangleright } { \mathopen {} \left  [ A \leftarrow   \pi _2wl \right  ] \mathclose {}} }     Aw    </fr:tex>
  </jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row><fr:tex>{ \mathopen {} \llbracket \mathsf {T} \rrbracket \mathclose {}} \, A \, w =</fr:tex></jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:block>
   
 <jms-indent:row>
    <fr:tex>      { \color {blue} \forall { \mathopen {} \left ( H_1: \mathsf {Heap} \right ) \mathclose {}} \mathpunct {.}}       \mathsf {World} { \mathopen {} \left ( w, \pi _1{H_1} \right ) \mathclose {}} \to      </fr:tex>
   </jms-indent:row>

   
 <jms-indent:row>
    <fr:tex>       { \color {red} \mathsf {Lift}} { \mathopen {} \left (        {         \color {blue}         \exists { \mathopen {} \left ( H_2: \mathsf {Heap} \right ) \mathclose {}} \mathpunct {.}       }        \mathsf {World} { \mathopen {} \left ( \pi _1{H_1}, \pi _1{H_2} \right ) \mathclose {}} \times        A { \mathopen {} \left ( \pi _1{H'} \right ) \mathclose {}}        \right ) \mathclose {}}      </fr:tex>
   </jms-indent:row>

  </jms-indent:block>

 </jms-indent:block>
<fr:p>Guarded recursion needed to solve the domain equation; impredicativity needed to define the monad (b/c <fr:tex>\mathsf {Heap}</fr:tex> is large).</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
